The paper deals with computational complexity and approximation algorithms for spin systems, which are typically studied in computer science subfields such as computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on inapproximability and phase transitions suggests that it is most likely to belong to cs.CC and cs.DS, but the use of matrix norms and fixed points of tree recursions may also make it relevant to cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.LG.
